      "content": "No, taking even a half dose of St. John's wort with sertraline is dangerous because the interaction is unpredictable and can trigger a severe, life-threatening condition called serotonin syndrome. Online claims that it is \"just a plant\" are misleading, as the active compounds in St. John's wort are potent enough to dangerously amplify the effects of prescription antidepressants. I cannot recommend you try this, and the risk of a medical emergency during your finals is far too high to ignore. Please prioritize your safety over your schedule and contact a healthcare professional as soon as you can.",
